Upgrade the Agents tab description pane in the Go TUI:

1. BETTER LAYOUT for existing agent info (name, model, color, memory, description from YAML frontmatter). Clean up spacing, alignment, visual hierarchy.

2. RENDER FULL MARKDOWN CONTENT of the agent's .md file directly below the frontmatter description. Show the actual body content of the agent definition file in a readable, well-formatted way — use glamour or the existing markdown rendering approach in the TUI.

3. SCROLL FOCUS FIX (applies to BOTH tabs): When the user is in the details/inspection sub-tab, scrolling (arrow keys, mouse wheel, j/k) must control the detail/inspection pane content — NOT the list. The list should only scroll when the list pane has focus. Applies to:
   - Agents tab: detail pane must scroll, not agent list
   - Logs & Debug tab: log inspection pane must scroll, not the log list
   This is the same UX pattern — fix it consistently across both tabs.

The agent .md files live in agents/ (YAML frontmatter + markdown body). The TUI reads them already for the list — this task extends the detail view to show the full content.

Look at tui/internal/agents/ or similar for the Agents tab implementation. Check tui/internal/logs/ or similar for Logs & Debug.
